Lieutenant Colonel Dimakatso Mooi confirmed the incident saying that "the community members want the foreigners out of their village after one of the foreigners allegedly stabbed a 16-year-old boy to death" on Saturday.The stabbing occurred at Bankhara Bodulong and the foreign shop-owner accused of killing the teen was arrested.Mooi said that four suspects had been arrested for malicious damage to property and 50 foreign nationals had been taken to a place of safety.Police are monitoring the situation in Bankhara Bodulong.Members of the community arrested for looting will appear in court on Thursday. - TMG Digital